Half a century ago, China and the UK agreed to exchange ambassadors, opening a new chapter in their relationship. Looking back, both have come a long way and achieved fruitful results. Fifty years ago, yearly bilateral trade was only $300 million, but last year, it exceeded $100 billion for the first time. Today, as we experience unprecedented challenges globally, China-UK relations are set to reach a new historical juncture in the future. In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Michelle Van den Bergh explores the possibilities in store.